OL,6,FThe report said since 2014, alcoholic
OL,7,Fliver diseases had accounted for
OL,8,Faround two-thirds of alcohol-specific
OL,9,Fdeaths, decreasing from 68.5% in 2014
OL,10,Fto 64.7% in 2024.
OL,12,FMental and behavioural disorders
OL,13,Fcaused by use of alcohol had been the
OL,14,Fsecond-most common cause of death
OL,15,Famong alcohol-specific deaths over the
OL,16,Fsame period, accounting for 15.4% of
OL,17,Falcohol-specific deaths in 2024.
