OL,6,F"It is a cost-effective way to tackle
OL,7,Falcohol-related harms and reduce
OL,8,Fhealth inequalities, particularly
OL,9,Famong populations in more deprived
OL,10,Fareas which, according to these latest
OL,11,Fstatistics, have four times as many
OL,12,Falcohol-specific deaths compared to
OL,13,Fthe least deprived areas."
OL,15,FDr Corrigan added: "Alongside MUP
OL,16,Flegislation, it is essential that
OL,17,Fthere is help available for those who
OL,18,Fwant to address their drinking.
